Worshippers at the Methodist Church of Southern Africa in the Meadowlands neighbourhood of Soweto take part in a prayer. JOHANNESBURG - The Methodist Church has decided not to reopen during level three of the lockdown. The church is encouraging believers to keep the current status quo by continuing to exercise caution and praying at home. The Methodist Church joins the Zion Christian Church which is also not opening during level three. WATCH: Ramaphosa meets religious leaders amid COVID-19 The ZCC says it's still too early, and unsafe to resume services. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that religious gatherings under strict regulations would be allowed when the country enters level three on Monday. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.